tasks.description:
Check Gmail inbox for NEW UNREAD emails using Gmail's built-in Gemini AI and display the results in a generative UI widget. Only show emails that haven't been shown in a previous run.

The CDP script is at: /Users/joemccann/.pi/agent/git/github.com/pasky/chrome-cdp-skill/skills/chrome-cdp/scripts/cdp.mjs
Chrome app is at: '/Applications/Chrome Debug.app' (should already be running with remote debugging on port 9222).
Seen-emails state file: /Users/joemccann/dev/apps/util/browse-cdp/.pi/gmail-seen.json

Steps:

1. LOAD PREVIOUSLY SEEN EMAILS
   Read the file at /Users/joemccann/dev/apps/util/browse-cdp/.pi/gmail-seen.json
   It contains a JSON object: { "seenThreadIds": ["19cfc448244df063", ...] }
   Thread IDs are hex strings from Gmail's data-legacy-thread-id attribute.
   If the file doesn't exist, treat seenThreadIds as an empty array.
   NOTE: If the file contains old-format numeric IDs (like "1859920985253081187"), ignore them
   during comparison — they won't match the new hex format and that's fine (those emails will
   be treated as new on the first run after this migration, which is acceptable).

2. FIND THE GMAIL TAB
   Run the CDP script with: list
   Look for a tab with url containing 'mail.google.com'. Use its target ID prefix.
   If no Gmail tab exists, navigate any tab to https://mail.google.com/mail/u/0/#inbox

3. NAVIGATE TO INBOX
   Run the CDP script with: nav <target> https://mail.google.com/mail/u/0/#inbox
   Wait 5 seconds for the page to fully load (Gmail's dynamic rendering needs extra time).
   Then verify emails are loaded by running CDP eval: document.querySelectorAll('tr.zA').length
   If the count is 0, wait another 3 seconds and check again (up to 3 retries).

4. EXTRACT UNREAD EMAILS WITH THREAD IDs AND LINKS
   IMPORTANT: Use the `data-legacy-thread-id` attribute (hex format like '19cfc5c03dc0ed4a') for both
   the threadId (used for seen-state tracking) and the Gmail link URL. The numeric thread IDs from
   jslog do NOT work in Gmail URLs — they produce 'conversation no longer exists' errors.
   Run CDP eval on the Gmail tab with this JS (all as one expression):
   ```
   var rows = document.querySelectorAll('tr.zA');
   var emails = [];
   for (var i = 0; i < rows.length; i++) {
     var row = rows[i];
     if (!row.classList.contains('zE')) continue;
     var sender = row.querySelector('.yW .bA4 span') || row.querySelector('.yW span[email]') || row.querySelector('.yW');
     var subject = row.querySelector('.bog');
     var snippet = row.querySelector('.y2');
     var timeSpan = row.querySelector('span[title]');
     var legacyEl = row.querySelector('[data-legacy-thread-id]');
     var threadId = legacyEl ? legacyEl.getAttribute('data-legacy-thread-id') : '';
     emails.push({
       sender: sender ? sender.textContent.trim() : 'Unknown',
       subject: subject ? subject.textContent.trim() : '(no subject)',
       snippet: snippet ? snippet.textContent.trim().replace(/^- /, '') : '',
       time: timeSpan ? timeSpan.getAttribute('title') || timeSpan.textContent.trim() : '',
       threadId: threadId,
       link: threadId ? 'https://mail.google.com/mail/u/0/#inbox/' + threadId : ''
     });
   }
   JSON.stringify(emails);
   ```

5. FILTER OUT PREVIOUSLY SEEN EMAILS
   From the extracted email list, remove any email whose threadId appears in the seenThreadIds array loaded in step 1.
   If NO new emails remain after filtering, skip steps 6-8, just call complete_task and exit.

6. GET GMAIL GEMINI AI SUMMARIES (only if there are new emails)
   a) Click the 'Ask Gmail' search input. Use CDP eval to find it:
      var input = document.querySelector('input[aria-label="Ask Gmail"]');
      Get its bounding rect and click it with clickxy.
   b) Type the query using CDP type: "summarize my unread emails"
   c) Press Enter using CDP evalraw:
      Input.dispatchKeyEvent {"type":"keyDown","key":"Enter","code":"Enter","windowsVirtualKeyCode":13}
      Input.dispatchKeyEvent {"type":"keyUp","key":"Enter","code":"Enter","windowsVirtualKeyCode":13}
   d) Wait 5 seconds for the AI Overview to generate.
   e) Click 'Show more' if visible. Find it with:
      var showMore = [...document.querySelectorAll('*')].find(function(el) { return el.textContent.trim() === 'Show more' && el.offsetWidth > 0; });
      Click it if found, then wait 1 second.
   f) Extract the AI summary text using CDP eval:
      var all = document.querySelectorAll('*');
      var aiSection = null;
      for (var i = 0; i < all.length; i++) {
        if (all[i].textContent.trim().startsWith('Here is a summary')) {
          aiSection = all[i];
          break;
        }
      }
      aiSection ? aiSection.innerText : 'No AI summary available';

7. PARSE AI SUMMARIES AND MATCH TO EMAILS
   The Gemini AI Overview text contains bullet-style summaries like:
   "TopicOrSender: Summary sentence. ReferenceNumber"
   Parse each line and match to the new emails by sender name or subject keywords.
   For each email, use the matched AI summary. If no match, fall back to the snippet.

8. NAVIGATE BACK TO INBOX
   Run the CDP script with: nav <target> https://mail.google.com/mail/u/0/#inbox

9. UPDATE SEEN STATE
   Write the updated seen-emails file at /Users/joemccann/dev/apps/util/browse-cdp/.pi/gmail-seen.json
   Add all threadIds from the NEW emails (the ones you're about to display) to the seenThreadIds array.
   Keep the old seenThreadIds too. Cap the array at 500 entries (trim oldest first) to prevent unbounded growth.
   Write the file using the write tool.

10. DISPLAY IN GENERATIVE UI WIDGET (only if there are new emails)
    Use the show_widget tool (call visualize_read_me first if not already called this session).
    Widget specs:
    - title: 'gmail_inbox'
    - Size: 1200x800
    - floating: true (always on top)

    THEME / LIGHT-DARK MODE:
    The widget MUST include a light/dark mode system with these requirements:
    - Default to the OS/system color scheme using: window.matchMedia('(prefers-color-scheme: dark)')
    - Include a toggle button in the top-right of the header bar (use ☀️ for light mode active, 🌙 for dark mode active)
    - Clicking the toggle switches between light and dark mode immediately
    - The toggle state should persist in localStorage key 'gmail-widget-theme' so it survives widget refreshes
    - Also listen for OS theme changes with matchMedia.addEventListener('change', ...) to auto-switch if user hasn't manually toggled
    - Use CSS custom properties (variables) on :root for all colors so the switch is instant with no flicker

    CSS variables to define for DARK mode:
      --bg: #1a1a1a; --bg-surface: #242424; --bg-hover: #2a2a2a;
      --text: #e0e0e0; --text-muted: #999; --text-dim: #666;
      --border: #333; --accent: #6ea8fe; --accent-hover: #8bb9ff;
      --badge-bg: #2d2d2d; --row-unread-border: #4a9eff;
      --header-bg: #111; --footer-bg: #111;

    CSS variables to define for LIGHT mode:
      --bg: #ffffff; --bg-surface: #f8f9fa; --bg-hover: #f0f1f3;
      --text: #1a1a1a; --text-muted: #666; --text-dim: #999;
      --border: #e0e0e0; --accent: #1a73e8; --accent-hover: #1557b0;
      --badge-bg: #e8f0fe; --row-unread-border: #1a73e8;
      --header-bg: #f8f9fa; --footer-bg: #f8f9fa;

    Apply all these variables everywhere in the CSS — background-color: var(--bg), color: var(--text), etc.
    The toggle button itself should be styled as a small pill/chip in the header: border-radius: 20px, padding: 4px 12px, background: var(--badge-bg), cursor: pointer, no border, font-size: 14px.

    LAYOUT AND TABLE:
    - Header: '📧 New Unread Emails' left-aligned, 'Last checked: <timestamp>' center, theme toggle + ✨ Gemini badge right
    - Show count: 'N new emails since last check'
    - Table columns:
      • Sender (bold, color: var(--text))
      • Subject (clickable link using the email's link URL, color: var(--accent), hover: var(--accent-hover); target="_blank")
      • AI Summary (from Gemini, prefixed with ✨, color: var(--text-muted))
      • Time (color: var(--text-dim), white-space: nowrap)
    - All rows: border-left: 3px solid var(--row-unread-border); background: var(--bg-surface)
    - Row hover: background: var(--bg-hover)
    - Table: width 100%, border-collapse: collapse, th/td padding: 10px 14px
    - Table header: background var(--header-bg), text-transform uppercase, font-size 11px, letter-spacing 0.5px, color var(--text-muted)
    - Footer: 'Powered by Gmail Gemini AI · Next refresh in 10 minutes', background var(--footer-bg), color var(--text-dim), centered, padding 12px, font-size 12px
    - If the widget window titled 'gmail_inbox' is already open, it will update via morphdom.

IMPORTANT: After completing all steps, call complete_task with id "gmail-inbox-monitor" to mark this run done so it fires again on the next 10-minute interval.
